cyan【🩵】resident weeb・rap nerd 2025-03-01 6:32 AM
here's an explanation for dummies from copilot:
MLM stands for Multi-Level Marketing. Imagine you have a product to sell, like a fancy lotion. In a traditional business, you'd sell this lotion directly to customers or through stores. But in an MLM, you sell the lotion to people who then sell it to other people. How It Works: Join the MLM: You sign up to be a distributor for the company. Sell Products: You sell products to customers and earn a commission. Recruit Others: You invite others to join the MLM and become distributors. Earn From Recruits: When the people you recruit sell products, you earn a percentage of their sales. And if they recruit others, you can earn from those sales too. So, the idea is that you make money not only by selling products but also by building a team of distributors. It creates multiple levels of earnings, hence the name Multi-Level Marketing.
